In **Java**, functions are called **methods**. There are several types based on parameters and return values.

---

## 🔹 1. Based on Parameters & Return Type

### ✅ (a) No Parameters, No Return Value

* Takes nothing, returns nothing

```java
void greet() {
    System.out.println("Hello");
}
```

---

### ✅ (b) No Parameters, With Return Value

* Takes nothing, but returns something

```java
int getNumber() {
    return 10;
}
```

---

### ✅ (c) With Parameters, No Return Value

* Takes input, but returns nothing

```java
void add(int a, int b) {
    System.out.println(a + b);
}
```

---

### ✅ (d) With Parameters, With Return Value

* Takes input and returns result

```java
int add(int a, int b) {
    return a + b;
}
```

---

## 🔹 2. Based on Behavior

### ✅ (a) Static Method

* Belongs to class (no object needed)

```java
static void show() {
    System.out.println("Static method");
}
```

---

### ✅ (b) Instance Method

* Requires object to call

```java
void display() {
    System.out.println("Instance method");
}
```

---

### ✅ (c) Constructor (Special Method)

* Used to initialize object

```java
class Test {
    Test() {
        System.out.println("Constructor called");
    }
}
```

---

### ✅ (d) Abstract Method

* Declared but not defined (used in abstract class/interface)

```java
abstract void run();
```

---

### ✅ (e) Final Method

* Cannot be overridden

```java
final void show() {
    System.out.println("Final method");
}
```

---

## 🔹 3. Other Important Types

### ✅ Method Overloading

* Same method name, different parameters

```java
int add(int a, int b) { return a + b; }
int add(int a, int b, int c) { return a + b + c; }
```

---

### ✅ Method Overriding

* Redefining parent class method in child class

---

## 🔥 Summary (Easy Way)

| Type                     | Meaning               |
| ------------------------ | --------------------- |
| No parameter / No return | Simple print          |
| No parameter / Return    | Gives output          |
| Parameter / No return    | Takes input           |
| Parameter / Return       | Best (input + output) |
| Static                   | Class level           |
| Instance                 | Object level          |

